s even though they're newly added to the source.\n\nThe transform is configured with a 1-second delay on the @timestamp field, meaning it should only process data up to 1 second before the current time. I need to check whether the trigger count and documents processed metrics have increased to determine if the transform is actively picking up these new documents or if there's a lag in the processing pipeline. So continuous transforms only process data within a specific time window—documents with timestamps before the previous checkpoint's upper bound won't be reprocessed. Since my new documents are timestamped at midnight on June 25th, which is well before the checkpoint 1 upper bound of 01:52:08, they fall outside the range that checkpoint 2 will examine.\n\nI need to create documents with timestamps after that checkpoint boundary to actually trigger the transform to advance.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":694,"cache_read_input_tokens":71651,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":694},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9578eac4-901e-472f-b1bf-ce452e0389a3","uuid":"7549f2ef-9102-4c00-8593-d90f5b7c111d","request_id":"req_011CcPAeAfYgsQ755RxhwYFi"}
